actText>&lt;p>The purpose of the seminar is to outline and evaluate the role and impact of private sector businesses in contributing to urban regeneration, with a focus on New Labour?s sustainable communities programme. This is the broad theme of the studentship. The seminar will discuss three areas of debate, of interest both to business and government:&lt;/p>

&lt;ol>
 

 &lt;li>What knowledge do businesses have of urban regeneration plans and policies, and how do such policies and plans influence business plans and behaviour?&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>What are the motives for business involvement in urban regeneration? How can these be developed and harnessed?&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>What factors are likely to inhibit or prevent business involvement in sustainable community building?&lt;/li>

&lt;/ol>

